  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Basel III banking regulations\n\n2. National Legislations:\n- United States Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- UK Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations in multiple countries\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures:\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Financial institution compliance obligations\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory approaches and international collaboration.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
